{"topics":[{"topicLabel":"Categories and varieties","topicThesaurusName":"topics","topicUrl":"http://dictionary.cambridge.org/topics/comparing-and-classifying/categories-and-varieties/","topicId":"categories-and-varieties","topicParentId":"comparing-and-classifying"}],"dictionaryCode":"american-english","entryLabel":"style","entryContent":"<di><header><title>style<\/title><\/header> <pos-block><header><info><posgram><pos>noun<\/pos><\/posgram> <audio type=\"pronunciation\" region=\"us\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"https://dictionary.cambridge.org/media/american-english/us_pron/s/sty/style/style.mp3\"/><source type=\"audio/ogg\" src=\"https://dictionary.cambridge.org/media/american-english/us_pron_ogg/s/sty/style/style.ogg\"/><\/audio> <pron>/<ipa>stɑɪl<\/ipa>/<\/pron> <\/info><\/header><sense-block><header><title>WAY<\/title><\/header> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <gram>[<gcs><gc>C/U<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info> <def>a way of doing something, esp. one that is typical of a person, group of people, place, or time: <\/def><\/definition><examp><info><gram>[<gcs><gc>C<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info><eg>Puente fused Latin with other musical styles.<\/eg><\/examp><examp><info><gram>[<gcs><gc>C<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info><eg>The book is written in the style of an 18th-century novel.<\/eg><\/examp><examp><info><gram>[<gcs><gc>U<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info><eg>His portraits were awkward in style.<\/eg><\/examp><\/def-block> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <gram>[<gcs><gc>C/U<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info> <def>Style is also a special quality that makes a person or thing seem different and attractive: <\/def><\/definition><examp><info><gram>[<gcs><gc>U<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info><eg>I like this team \u2013 the players have style.<\/eg><\/examp><\/def-block><\/sense-block> <sense-block><header><title>DESIGN<\/title><\/header> <def-block><definition><info><lvl>\u203a<\/lvl> <gram>[<gcs><gc>C<\/gc><\/gcs>]<\/gram><\/info> <def>a particu